## Overview

For users without Apple Silicon, Hermetic provides cloud training backends:

| Backend | Platform | Best For | Status |
|---------|----------|----------|--------|
| Unsloth Modal | Modal.com (GPU cloud) | Fastest LoRA, 2-5x speedup | Production |
| Axolotl | Any NVIDIA GPU | Nous/Hermes parity, full YAML config | Production |
| MLX-Tune | Apple Silicon only | Local, private, free | Production |

## Unsloth Modal

[Modal](https://modal.com) provides serverless GPU compute. Unsloth is optimized for fast LoRA.

### Setup

```bash
pip install modal
modal token new
modal run modal_worker.py test_gpu
```

### Running

```bash
hermetic train ./data -c hermetic.yaml
```

### Modal GPU Options

| GPU | VRAM | Cost/hr | Best For |
|-----|------|---------|----------|
| T4 | 16GB | $0.73 | Small models, testing |
| A10G | 24GB | $1.30 | 7B-13B models |
| A100 | 40GB | $2.50 | Large models, speed |
| H100 | 80GB | $4.50 | Fastest, 70B+ models |

## Axolotl

[Axolotl](https://github.com/OpenAccess-AI-Collective/axolotl) is the standard for Hermes/Mistral training.

### Setup

```bash
pip install axolotl
```

See Axolotl documentation for full configuration options.

## Backend Comparison

MLX-Tune: Apple Silicon, 250 tok/s M1 Max, QLoRA, CLI YAML, High parity, GGUF limited, Free local
Unsloth Modal: NVIDIA Modal, 1000 tok/s H100, QLoRA, CLI YAML, High parity, GGUF Yes, Pay-per-use
Axolotl: NVIDIA local/cloud, 800 tok/s A100, QLoRA LoRA, Full YAML, Native parity, GGUF Yes, Free local / Cloud

## Choosing a Backend

Apple Silicon (M1-M4 Max/Ultra) -> MLX-Tune (free, local, private)
NVIDIA GPU + want speed -> Unsloth Modal (pay-per-use)
NVIDIA GPU + need Hermes parity -> Axolotl (full control)
No GPU, want cloud -> Unsloth Modal (serverless)
Enterprise / Compliance -> Axolotl on-prem

## Multi-Backend Config

```text
# hermetic.yaml - switch backends via env
train:
  backend: "${HERMETIC_BACKEND:-mlx-tune}"
  model: "${HERMETIC_MODEL:-mlx-community/Qwen3-8B-4bit}"
```

Local:
```bash
HERMETIC_BACKEND=mlx-tune hermetic train ./data
```

Cloud:
```bash
HERMETIC_BACKEND=unsloth-modal HERMETIC_MODEL=unsloth/Qwen3-8B-bnb-4bit hermetic train ./data
```

